content: I don't have the capacity to have personal favorites or opinions, but some of the most popular songs and timeless classics of early rock and roll include "johnny b. goode" by chuck berry, "blue suede shoes" by elvis presley, "tutti frutti" by little richard, "great balls of fire" by jerry lee lewis, and "peggy sue" by buddy holly. these songs are still enjoyed and revered by music fans around the world today.
